    "body": "Some functions are not overridden by an (cython-provided) derived classes, and we almost certainly don't want them to be overridden by any user-defined base classes.  Therefore avoid call directly rather than going through the vtab.\r\n\r\nA few notes:\r\n* `memoryview` `convert_item_to_object` `assign_item_from_object` `_get_base` are excluded because the `_memoryviewslice` does deliberately override them.\r\n* Ideally I'd use `cython.final` to be explicit, however that interacts badly with the `cname` decorator and generates invalid code without the `cname`. That doesn't seem worth fixing for this minor use although in principle I could try to.\r\n* For `array` we ideally wouldn't generate the vtabs struct at all (however `cython.final` wouldn't achieve this). For `memoryview` we have to generate the vtab struct for binary compatibility.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-07T17:43:43Z",
