                    "name": "da-woods"
                },
                "message": "Avoid some vtab calls in memoryview utility code\n\nSome functions are not overridden by an (cython-provided)\nderived classes, and we almost certainly don't want them to be\noverridden by any user-defined base classes.  Therefore avoid\ncall directly rather than going through the vtab.\n\nA few notes:\n* `memoryview` `convert_item_to_object` `assign_item_from_object`\n  `_get_base` are excluded because the `_memoryviewslice` does\n  deliberately override them.\n* Ideally I'd use `cython.final` to be explicit, however that\n  interacts badly with the `cname` decorator. That doesn't seem\n  worth fixing for this minor use although in principle I could\n  try to.\n* For `array` we ideally wouldn't generate the vtabs struct at\n  all (however `cython.final` wouldn't achieve this). For\n  `memoryview` we have to generate the vtab struct for binary\n  compatibility.",
